==English==

===Etymology===
{{ME.}} [[wargeld]], from [[w:Old English language|Old English]][[category:Words of Old English language origin]] [[ƿergeld]], compound of [[ƿer]], ''man'' + [[geld]], ''payment''.

===Alternative spellings===
*[[weregeld]]
*[[weregild]]
*[[wergild]]

===Noun===
'''wergeld'''
# {{archaic}}: In Anglo-Saxon and Germanic law, a reparational payment usually demanded of a person guilty of homicide or other serious crimes.

